 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Iltraendar D`Luminos</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> I'm in no way a PvP master, I've only dueled twice and I'm level 42... that should tell you something.  </P><P>BUT, in my opinion, I would try this.</P><P>His downfall will be the fact that he's only got around 500hp, give or take.  I would start with fear asap, don't bother with darkness, but try to make sure you're in a zone with bad pathing so he won't get too far ahead of you.  Lay on heat blood/flutter/vampiric curse.  Re-fear just for good measure, then sit down and watch him die.  If you're lucky his pet will be a non issue, it probably will not hit you hard enough to interrupt your casting.  Let your pet deal with his pet to keep it off of you if you like.</P><P>As far as charm, well, if he can charm you before you get fear to stick, you're in trouble.  If he charms your pet, /laugh at him and continue with the original strategy.</P><P>Another useful tool is to start the fight by using shadow step.  He will not be able to cast charm before you cast SS, and when you do it he'll have to re-target you, giving you valuable time to cast fear.  A tip of shadow step though, make sure you are at the highest point possible, as it will transport you further away.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>RestlessSZ</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Beating the level 28 chanter should not be a problem (I play a 51 chanter on SZ, hehe).</P><P>Get your Magic Resist to something close to 130 (crafted items, like dimond gear if you can afford, Jacinth finger rings, other MR gear like a Blackened Wand, Hollowed Bone Bracer, don't forget your self buffs, etc...).</P><P>At his level he can cast 3 spells on you:<BR>-Tash<BR>-Dispell<BR>-Chaotic Feedback</P><P>You will resist all other spells. Your pet will not have the MR gear, so he might be the target of his spells, but who cares, lol.<BR>I bet he got crappy resist gear, so go for any DoT/DD you want.</P><P>With high MR you just cannot loose the fight. You don't even need your pet. Fear, Root or Scream the chanter pet, then lay a few DoTs on the player. Nothing he can do against that.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
